Communication between Azure Virtual Networks and on-premises resources is widely used in hybrid cloud architectures.

For example, a company can connect its office network to Azure using a Site-to-Site VPN, allowing employees to access cloud-hosted applications as if they were local.

A real-life use case is an enterprise ERP system where part of the system is hosted on-premises and part in Azure. Both environments communicate seamlessly.

Another example is backup and disaster recovery, where on-premise servers replicate data to Azure for redundancy.

Additionally, organizations use ExpressRoute for high-speed, private connectivity when handling sensitive financial or healthcare data.

These setups allow gradual cloud adoption while maintaining existing infrastructure.
